# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Dog Agent — Crontab Example
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Install with: crontab cron/crontab.example
# Or edit:      crontab -e
#
# All paths assume the project is at /home/pi/projects/dog-agent (adjust as
# needed for your setup). Logs are written to cron_logs/ for debugging.
#
# ─── Daily report (every day at 21:00) ──────────────────────────────────────
# Generates a behavior summary and sends via Telegram (or prints to stdout).
# Also triggers a health snapshot at the same time.
#
0 21 * * * cd /home/pi/projects/dog-agent && ./cron/daily_report.sh >> cron_logs/daily_report.log 2>&1

# ─── Health check (every 30 minutes) ────────────────────────────────────────
# Queries the health endpoint and forwards any active alerts to alert_manager.
#
*/30 * * * * cd /home/pi/projects/dog-agent && ./cron/health_check.sh >> cron_logs/health_check.log 2>&1

# ─── Battery check (every 60 minutes) ───────────────────────────────────────
# Reads battery voltage and alerts if below 3.4V (LiPo threshold).
#
0 * * * * cd /home/pi/projects/dog-agent && ./cron/battery_alert.sh >> cron_logs/battery_alert.log 2>&1

# ─── Optional: Log rotation placeholder ───────────────────────────────────────
# The data_logger handles its own retention — cron jobs log to cron_logs/
# which you may want to rotate with logrotate or a monthly cleanup rule.
#
# Example cleanup (runs 1st of month, removes logs older than 90 days):
# 0 0 1 * * find /home/pi/projects/dog-agent/cron_logs -name '*.log' -mtime +90 -delete